ÅòµU<?php exit; ?>a:1:{s:7:"content";a:137:{s:10:"_edit_last";a:1:{i:0;s:1:"1";}s:10:"_edit_lock";a:1:{i:0;s:12:"1437620194:1";}s:17:"_wp_page_template";a:1:{i:0;s:27:"templates/staff_members.php";}s:36:"add_a_new_staff_member_0_member_name";a:1:{i:0;s:14:"Dr Peta Lilley";}s:37:"_add_a_new_staff_member_0_member_name";a:1:{i:0;s:19:"field_55acc3e8641a1";}s:37:"add_a_new_staff_member_0_member_title";a:1:{i:0;s:21:"Clinical Psychologist";}s:38:"_add_a_new_staff_member_0_member_title";a:1:{i:0;s:19:"field_55acc8bcc8efb";}s:50:"add_a_new_staff_member_0_member_list_0_member_logo";a:1:{i:0;s:2:"70";}s:51:"_add_a_new_staff_member_0_member_list_0_member_logo";a:1:{i:0;s:19:"field_55acc9ccc8efd";}s:36:"add_a_new_staff_member_0_member_list";a:1:{i:0;s:1:"1";}s:37:"_add_a_new_staff_member_0_member_list";a:1:{i:0;s:19:"field_55acc906c8efc";}s:35:"add_a_new_staff_member_0_member_bio";a:1:{i:0;s:402:"Peta completed the Clinical Psychology PhD Program within the School of Psychology, The University of Queensland (UQ). The focus of her research was the development of emotional and behavioural difficulties (particularly Post Traumatic Stress Disorder, PTSD) in children and adolescents following trauma. Peta has also completed a post-doctoral research fellow position in the School of Medicine at UQ.";}s:36:"_add_a_new_staff_member_0_member_bio";a:1:{i:0;s:19:"field_55acca62c8efe";}s:40:"add_a_new_staff_member_0_member_bio_more";a:1:{i:0;s:1710:"<p>Peta has worked in Government and non-government agencies, hospitals and private practice. Therapy has been conducted with children, adolescents, adults and families. While Petaâ€™s primary theoretical framework is Cognitive Behavioural Therapy (CBT), she utilises Schema-Focused therapy, Interpersonal Therapy (IPT), Mindfulness and Acceptance and Commitment Therapy (ACT) where appropriate. Peta is an accredited Triple P provider. Peta has full registration with the Australian Health Practitioner Regulation Agency (AHPRA). Peta is also a full member of the Australian Psychological Society (MAPS), and the APS College of Clinical Psychologists is recognised by Medicare as a provider of clinical psychology services. She is also a member of the Australian Association for Cognitive and Behaviour Therapy (AACBT) and is an accredited Triple P provider.</p>
<p>Prior to commencing PhD studies, Peta completed her Honours degree at the University of Queensland. Honours Class I in the field of Psychology was obtained. Peta also gained a Deanâ€™s commendation for academic achievement. A Bachelor of Arts degree, with a double major in psychology, was also awarded from the University of Queensland.</p>
<p>Peta has ongoing involvement in research and evidence-based practice. Peta also provides supervision for psychologists undergoing post-graduate training in Clinical Psychology at the School of Psychology (UQ). Peta has successfully completed the Supervisor Training and Accreditation Program (STAP).</p>
<p>Peta enjoys the arts, particularly dancing, running, reading, and spending time with family and friends. She is kept active by 3 young children and loves playing with them in the park.</p>";}s:41:"_add_a_new_staff_member_0_member_bio_more";a:1:{i:0;s:19:"field_55acca9bc8eff";}s:37:"add_a_new_staff_member_0_member_photo";a:1:{i:0;s:2:"71";}s:38:"_add_a_new_staff_member_0_member_photo";a:1:{i:0;s:19:"field_55accaeec8f00";}s:22:"add_a_new_staff_member";a:1:{i:0;s:1:"9";}s:23:"_add_a_new_staff_member";a:1:{i:0;s:19:"field_55acc37d641a0";}s:12:"banner_title";a:1:{i:0;s:0:"";}s:13:"_banner_title";a:1:{i:0;s:19:"field_55ac44b698abc";}s:10:"search_bar";a:1:{i:0;s:1:"1";}s:11:"_search_bar";a:1:{i:0;s:19:"field_55ac452d98abe";}s:36:"add_a_new_staff_member_1_member_name";a:1:{i:0;s:12:"Pauline Ryan";}s:37:"_add_a_new_staff_member_1_member_name";a:1:{i:0;s:19:"field_55acc3e8641a1";}s:37:"add_a_new_staff_member_1_member_title";a:1:{i:0;s:19:"Clinical Consultant";}s:38:"_add_a_new_staff_member_1_member_title";a:1:{i:0;s:19:"field_55acc8bcc8efb";}s:50:"add_a_new_staff_member_1_member_list_0_member_logo";a:1:{i:0;s:2:"70";}s:51:"_add_a_new_staff_member_1_member_list_0_member_logo";a:1:{i:0;s:19:"field_55acc9ccc8efd";}s:36:"add_a_new_staff_member_1_member_list";a:1:{i:0;s:1:"1";}s:37:"_add_a_new_staff_member_1_member_list";a:1:{i:0;s:19:"field_55acc906c8efc";}s:35:"add_a_new_staff_member_1_member_bio";a:1:{i:0;s:642:"Pauline is a clinical psychologist who completed her Master of Clinical Psychology at the University of Queensland. She is currently employed as a Clinical Consultant at Lilley Place Clinical Psychology. Her roles include providing clinical supervision, professional development and training to Lilley Place psychologists, and working on clinical service delivery to ensure that Lilley Place offers a first class service to clients, referrers and other professionals. In collaboration with the Clinic Director, she strives to ensure that Lilley Place is a fabulous environment for clients, professionals and the dedicated staff who work here.";}s:36:"_add_a_new_staff_member_1_member_bio";a:1:{i:0;s:19:"field_55acca62c8efe";}s:40:"add_a_new_staff_member_1_member_bio_more";a:1:{i:0;s:1662:"<p>Pauline has full registration with the Australian Health Practitioner Regulation Agency (AHPRA). She is also a full member of the Australian Psychological Society (MAPS), and the APS College of Clinical Psychologists and is recognised by Medicare as a provider of clinical psychology services. She is an accredited Level 5 Triple P provider.
<p>Pauline has practiced as a clinical psychologist since 2000.  She has worked at the Mater Childrenâ€™s Hospital Department of Paediatric Diabetes and Endocrinology, community Child and Youth Mental Health, the Mater Hospital Day Program, and as a private practitioner both for Lilley Place and herself.  She has a special interest in working with individuals and their support network to unravel the obstacles presented by the Autism Spectrum Disorders and Obsessive Compulsive Disorder.</p>
<p>Pauline has offered clinical supervision since 2004 and has Psychology Board of Australia Supervisor Training and Accreditation Program (STAP) approval.</p>
<p>Pauline views her role as a psychologist (whether that is direct client work, supervision or clinical consultancy) as a great privilege. She feels that it is immensely rewarding to support and help people faced by lifeâ€™s challenges.</p>
<p>Pauline works part time and balances her role as a psychologist with her role as a wife and mother to three unique growing boys. She is passionate about holistic health from the inside out.  Pauline aims for a healthy mind through the application of my clinical skills to her own life and a healthy body through nutrition, good sleep and exercise.</p>
<p>Pauline looks forward to meeting you at Lilley Place.</p>";}s:41:"_add_a_new_staff_member_1_member_bio_more";a:1:{i:0;s:19:"field_55acca9bc8eff";}s:37:"add_a_new_staff_member_1_member_photo";a:1:{i:0;s:2:"75";}s:38:"_add_a_new_staff_member_1_member_photo";a:1:{i:0;s:19:"field_55accaeec8f00";}s:36:"add_a_new_staff_member_2_member_name";a:1:{i:0;s:17:"Dr Zoe L. Barnett";}s:37:"_add_a_new_staff_member_2_member_name";a:1:{i:0;s:19:"field_55acc3e8641a1";}s:37:"add_a_new_staff_member_2_member_title";a:1:{i:0;s:51:"Clinical Psychologist and Clinical Geropsychologist";}s:38:"_add_a_new_staff_member_2_member_title";a:1:{i:0;s:19:"field_55acc8bcc8efb";}s:36:"add_a_new_staff_member_2_member_list";a:1:{i:0;s:1:"1";}s:37:"_add_a_new_staff_member_2_member_list";a:1:{i:0;s:19:"field_55acc906c8efc";}s:35:"add_a_new_staff_member_2_member_bio";a:1:{i:0;s:274:"Zoe has broad clinical experience across a diverse range of settings including private practice, public health, and community organisations. Her work includes psychological assessment and therapy with children, adults and older adults, in both individual and group settings.";}s:36:"_add_a_new_staff_member_2_member_bio";a:1:{i:0;s:19:"field_55acca62c8efe";}s:40:"add_a_new_staff_member_2_member_bio_more";a:1:{i:0;s:1774:"<p>Her areas of interest include the treatment of depression, anxiety, panic, stress, trauma, addiction, low self-esteem, adjustment difficulties, grief and loss, pain management, the assessment and treatment of dementia, and general mental health across the lifespan.</p>
<p>Zoe uses a range of techniques and therapies with demonstrated effectiveness to assess, diagnose and treat her clientâ€™s mental health concerns. These include Cognitive Behavioural Therapy (CBT), Cognitive Processing Therapy (CPT), Acceptance and Commitment Therapy (ACT), Mindful based techniques and Motivational Interviewing. Each client is unique, and as such, Zoe develops specifically tailored interventions based on individual needs.</p>
<p>Zoe completed a Professional Doctorate in Clinical Psychology and Clinical Geropsychology at The University of Queensland (UQ) and attained multiple awards including Deanâ€™s Scholar. Zoe has guest lectured and tutored in the clinical psychology program at The University of Queensland. She has also been a guest speaker at conferences and special interest groups.</p>
<p>Zoeâ€™s research included the development of a correspondence based intervention for carers of older people with dementia. The Coping with Caring Program was designed to treat carerâ€™s high levels of stress, anxiety, and depressive symptoms.</p>
<p>Zoe holds full membership with the Australian Health Practitioner Regulation Agency (AHPRA), and is recognised by Medicare as a provider of clinical psychology services. She is a full member of the Australian Psychological Society (APS) and the APS College of Clinical Psychologists (CClin). Zoe is also a member of the Psychology Ageing Interest Group (PAIG) and is published in the journal of Aging and Mental Health.</p>";}s:41:"_add_a_new_staff_member_2_member_bio_more";a:1:{i:0;s:19:"field_55acca9bc8eff";}s:37:"add_a_new_staff_member_2_member_photo";a:1:{i:0;s:2:"78";}s:38:"_add_a_new_staff_member_2_member_photo";a:1:{i:0;s:19:"field_55accaeec8f00";}s:50:"add_a_new_staff_member_2_member_list_0_member_logo";a:1:{i:0;s:2:"70";}s:51:"_add_a_new_staff_member_2_member_list_0_member_logo";a:1:{i:0;s:19:"field_55acc9ccc8efd";}s:36:"add_a_new_staff_member_3_member_name";a:1:{i:0;s:17:"Dr Rachel Bushing";}s:37:"_add_a_new_staff_member_3_member_name";a:1:{i:0;s:19:"field_55acc3e8641a1";}s:37:"add_a_new_staff_member_3_member_title";a:1:{i:0;s:21:"Clinical Psychologist";}s:38:"_add_a_new_staff_member_3_member_title";a:1:{i:0;s:19:"field_55acc8bcc8efb";}s:50:"add_a_new_staff_member_3_member_list_0_member_logo";a:1:{i:0;s:2:"70";}s:51:"_add_a_new_staff_member_3_member_list_0_member_logo";a:1:{i:0;s:19:"field_55acc9ccc8efd";}s:36:"add_a_new_staff_member_3_member_list";a:1:{i:0;s:1:"1";}s:37:"_add_a_new_staff_member_3_member_list";a:1:{i:0;s:19:"field_55acc906c8efc";}s:35:"add_a_new_staff_member_3_member_bio";a:1:{i:0;s:606:"Rachel is a Clinical Psychologist who has extensive experience working with children and families. Her passionate and creative approach helps to bring fun into the therapy setting. Rachel specialises in the assessment and treatment of psychological disorders that impact on children, adolescents, adults and families. She has worked in mental health services both in Australia and the United Kingdom, and has extensive training and experience working with family members and systems who have been impacted by trauma. She has a special interest in parent-child relationships and early emotional development.";}s:36:"_add_a_new_staff_member_3_member_bio";a:1:{i:0;s:19:"field_55acca62c8efe";}s:40:"add_a_new_staff_member_3_member_bio_more";a:1:{i:0;s:1273:"<p>She uses a range of therapeutic approaches including Cognitive-Behavioural Therapy, Schema Therapy, Play Therapy, Mindfulness, and parenting interventions including Triple P (Accredited Facilitator) and Dyadic Developmental Psychotherapy.</p>
<p>Rachel has developed and delivered education and training programs, and has been highly involved in group facilitation, the development of psychoeducational resources, and therapeutic program development. She is passionate about mental health and parenting education and early intervention, so that communities are strengthened through learning how to best help others.</p>
<p>Rachel holds a postgraduate Doctorate in Clinical Psychology, and she has a Clinical Endorsement with the Psychology Board of Australia (PsyBA). She is also a board-endorsed supervisor and has completed a Certificate IV in Training and Assessment. Her research background includes a doctoral research project on treatments for anxiety in children with Asperger Syndrome, and more recently she has contributed to a research project on health psychology and quality of life.</p>
<p>Her biggest education comes from running around after her sweet and boisterous two-year-old twins, and from her many failures at gardening, cooking, and sewing.</p>";}s:41:"_add_a_new_staff_member_3_member_bio_more";a:1:{i:0;s:19:"field_55acca9bc8eff";}s:37:"add_a_new_staff_member_3_member_photo";a:1:{i:0;s:2:"79";}s:38:"_add_a_new_staff_member_3_member_photo";a:1:{i:0;s:19:"field_55accaeec8f00";}s:36:"add_a_new_staff_member_4_member_name";a:1:{i:0;s:19:"Dr Elizabeth Goadby";}s:37:"_add_a_new_staff_member_4_member_name";a:1:{i:0;s:19:"field_55acc3e8641a1";}s:37:"add_a_new_staff_member_4_member_title";a:1:{i:0;s:21:"Clinical Psychologist";}s:38:"_add_a_new_staff_member_4_member_title";a:1:{i:0;s:19:"field_55acc8bcc8efb";}s:36:"add_a_new_staff_member_4_member_list";a:1:{i:0;s:1:"0";}s:37:"_add_a_new_staff_member_4_member_list";a:1:{i:0;s:19:"field_55acc906c8efc";}s:35:"add_a_new_staff_member_4_member_bio";a:1:{i:0;s:413:"Elizabeth is a clinical psychologist who holds a Doctorate of Clinical Psychology (Dpscyh)(Clin). Elizabeth has full registration with the Australian Health Practitioner Regulation Agency (AHPRA) and is recognized by Medicare as a provider of psychological services. Elizabeth is a member of the Association for Contextual Behavioural Science and an accredited provider of the Triple P Positive Parenting Program.";}s:36:"_add_a_new_staff_member_4_member_bio";a:1:{i:0;s:19:"field_55acca62c8efe";}s:40:"add_a_new_staff_member_4_member_bio_more";a:1:{i:0;s:789:"<p>Elizabeth has experience working within community, hospital and university clinic settings which have afforded her the opportunity to work with a broad range of psychological concerns including: depression, anxiety, adjustment difficulties, stress, self-harm, weight loss, behavioural difficulties and psychological issues associated with cancer.</p>
                <p>She enjoys working with children and adults and utilises Cognitive Behavioural Therapy and Acceptance and Commitment Therapy. Her research interests include the utility of parenting programs for behavioural difficulties and adjustment issues surrounding caregiver of individuals with Brain Tumour.</p>
                <p>In her spare time Elizabeth enjoys watching movies, reading and catching up with friends.</p>";}s:41:"_add_a_new_staff_member_4_member_bio_more";a:1:{i:0;s:19:"field_55acca9bc8eff";}s:37:"add_a_new_staff_member_4_member_photo";a:1:{i:0;s:2:"80";}s:38:"_add_a_new_staff_member_4_member_photo";a:1:{i:0;s:19:"field_55accaeec8f00";}s:36:"add_a_new_staff_member_5_member_name";a:1:{i:0;s:6:"El Raj";}s:37:"_add_a_new_staff_member_5_member_name";a:1:{i:0;s:19:"field_55acc3e8641a1";}s:37:"add_a_new_staff_member_5_member_title";a:1:{i:0;s:21:"Clinical Psychologist";}s:38:"_add_a_new_staff_member_5_member_title";a:1:{i:0;s:19:"field_55acc8bcc8efb";}s:36:"add_a_new_staff_member_5_member_list";a:1:{i:0;s:1:"1";}s:37:"_add_a_new_staff_member_5_member_list";a:1:{i:0;s:19:"field_55acc906c8efc";}s:35:"add_a_new_staff_member_5_member_bio";a:1:{i:0;s:977:"El has over a decade of experience in the field of Psychology. She uses a variety of approaches that she believes will be most effective based on both the issue she is working with and the experience she has in understanding what will best suit the person she is assisting. With a great passion in Psycho-education, Mindfulness Based Cognitive Behaviour Therapy, Acceptance and Commitment Therapy, Dialectical Behaviour Therapy, Motivational Interviewing, Solution Focussed Therapy, Positive Psychology, Emotion Focused Therapy and Schema Focused Therapy. El believes that much of our deeper present day struggles are linked to past experiences and perhaps the unresolved or non-addressed understandings or emotions associated with them. El also believes that often the issues presented in counselling are rather the symptoms of the underlining issue and hence it is often â€˜deeperâ€™ therapy as opposed to â€˜band aidâ€™ therapy that provides positive and sustainable change.";}s:36:"_add_a_new_staff_member_5_member_bio";a:1:{i:0;s:19:"field_55acca62c8efe";}s:40:"add_a_new_staff_member_5_member_bio_more";a:1:{i:0;s:618:"<p>Elâ€™s areas of interest include the treatment of Depression/Anxiety, Mood Disorders (Bipolar), Emotional Management &amp; Self Esteem, Grief and Loss, Pregnancy Counselling, Personality Disorders â€“ specifically Borderline Personality Disorder/Traits, Relationship issues/Couples therapy.</p>
                <p>El works with clients of all ages and feels that the ideal recipe for effective therapy is self-honesty, commitment and an authentic relationship between the therapist and client. Elâ€™s approach towards her clients would best be described as direct, challenging but also authentic and nurturing.</p>";}s:41:"_add_a_new_staff_member_5_member_bio_more";a:1:{i:0;s:19:"field_55acca9bc8eff";}s:37:"add_a_new_staff_member_5_member_photo";a:1:{i:0;s:2:"81";}s:38:"_add_a_new_staff_member_5_member_photo";a:1:{i:0;s:19:"field_55accaeec8f00";}s:36:"add_a_new_staff_member_6_member_name";a:1:{i:0;s:18:"Dr Alexander Short";}s:37:"_add_a_new_staff_member_6_member_name";a:1:{i:0;s:19:"field_55acc3e8641a1";}s:37:"add_a_new_staff_member_6_member_title";a:1:{i:0;s:29:"Clinical Psychology Registrar";}s:38:"_add_a_new_staff_member_6_member_title";a:1:{i:0;s:19:"field_55acc8bcc8efb";}s:50:"add_a_new_staff_member_6_member_list_0_member_logo";a:1:{i:0;s:2:"70";}s:51:"_add_a_new_staff_member_6_member_list_0_member_logo";a:1:{i:0;s:19:"field_55acc9ccc8efd";}s:36:"add_a_new_staff_member_6_member_list";a:1:{i:0;s:1:"1";}s:37:"_add_a_new_staff_member_6_member_list";a:1:{i:0;s:19:"field_55acc906c8efc";}s:35:"add_a_new_staff_member_6_member_bio";a:1:{i:0;s:691:"Alex completed his Doctor of Clinical Psychology (DClinPsych) at the University of Queensland. He has experience working in the public system, for non government organisations, universities, and in private practice. This has included work with children, adolescents, adults, and older adults with a variety of concerns including depression, anxiety disorders, alcohol and substance use problems, grief and loss, adjustment difficulties, bipolar disorder, schizophrenia, eating issues, personality disorders, autism spectrum disorders, learning disorders, and child behaviour problems. Alex has a specific interest in the treatment of post traumatic stress disorder (PTSD) and complex trauma.";}s:36:"_add_a_new_staff_member_6_member_bio";a:1:{i:0;s:19:"field_55acca62c8efe";}s:40:"add_a_new_staff_member_6_member_bio_more";a:1:{i:0;s:1146:"<p>Alex is trained in a variety of treatment approaches and tailors these to clientsâ€™ specific needs and preferences. These treatment approaches include Cognitive Behavioural Therapy, Schema Therapy, Emotion Focused Therapy, and Acceptance and Commitment Therapy.  Alex is an accredited provider of the Triple P Positive Parenting Program, The Secret Agent Society Social Skills Program, and has received specialist training in Trauma-Focused Cognitive Behavioural Therapy (TfCBT), Emotion Focused Couples Therapy (IFCT), and Motivational Interviewing (MI).</p>
                <p>Prior to completing his Doctorate, Alex graduated from a Bachelor of Arts majoring in Psychology with first class honours, and also completed a Bachelor of Business Management. He was awarded Deanâ€™s Commendations for High Achievement in every semester of his studies and is on the Deanâ€™s Honour Roll. Alex has full registration with the Australian Health Practitioner Regulation Agency (AHPRA).</p>
                <p>In his spare time Alex most enjoys spending time with his family and friends, and his passions include travel, sport, and the outdoors.</p>";}s:41:"_add_a_new_staff_member_6_member_bio_more";a:1:{i:0;s:19:"field_55acca9bc8eff";}s:37:"add_a_new_staff_member_6_member_photo";a:1:{i:0;s:2:"82";}s:38:"_add_a_new_staff_member_6_member_photo";a:1:{i:0;s:19:"field_55accaeec8f00";}s:36:"add_a_new_staff_member_7_member_name";a:1:{i:0;s:11:"Tara Taylor";}s:37:"_add_a_new_staff_member_7_member_name";a:1:{i:0;s:19:"field_55acc3e8641a1";}s:37:"add_a_new_staff_member_7_member_title";a:1:{i:0;s:21:"Clinical Psychologist";}s:38:"_add_a_new_staff_member_7_member_title";a:1:{i:0;s:19:"field_55acc8bcc8efb";}s:50:"add_a_new_staff_member_7_member_list_0_member_logo";a:1:{i:0;s:2:"70";}s:51:"_add_a_new_staff_member_7_member_list_0_member_logo";a:1:{i:0;s:19:"field_55acc9ccc8efd";}s:36:"add_a_new_staff_member_7_member_list";a:1:{i:0;s:1:"1";}s:37:"_add_a_new_staff_member_7_member_list";a:1:{i:0;s:19:"field_55acc906c8efc";}s:35:"add_a_new_staff_member_7_member_bio";a:1:{i:0;s:555:"Tara is a clinical psychologist who completed her Master of Clinical Psychology at Griffith University. She has experience working across community mental health, hospital and private practice settings with children, adolescents and adults. She works with clients with a variety of concerns including anxiety, depression, trauma, adjustment difficulties, eating issues, chronic pain, and behaviour problems. Tara has a particular passion for working with children and young people, and is an accredited provider of the Triple P Positive Parenting Program.";}s:36:"_add_a_new_staff_member_7_member_bio";a:1:{i:0;s:19:"field_55acca62c8efe";}s:40:"add_a_new_staff_member_7_member_bio_more";a:1:{i:0;s:776:"<p>Tara holds full registration with the Australian Health Practitioner Regulation Agency with endorsement as a Clinical Psychologist, and is recognised by Medicare as a provider of clinical psychology services. She uses a variety of approaches including Cognitive Behavioural Therapy, Acceptance and Commitment Therapy, Schema Therapy, and Narrative Therapy. Tara focuses on building warm, comfortable and collaborative relationships with clients to support them to achieve their goals. She also considers humour and fun to be an important part of the therapy process. Tara has a particular research interest in the adjustment and coping of parents of premature infants. In her spare time she enjoys having fun and keeping active with her young child and boisterous dogs.</p>";}s:41:"_add_a_new_staff_member_7_member_bio_more";a:1:{i:0;s:19:"field_55acca9bc8eff";}s:37:"add_a_new_staff_member_7_member_photo";a:1:{i:0;s:2:"83";}s:38:"_add_a_new_staff_member_7_member_photo";a:1:{i:0;s:19:"field_55accaeec8f00";}s:36:"add_a_new_staff_member_8_member_name";a:1:{i:0;s:15:"Dr Trevor Soole";}s:37:"_add_a_new_staff_member_8_member_name";a:1:{i:0;s:19:"field_55acc3e8641a1";}s:37:"add_a_new_staff_member_8_member_title";a:1:{i:0;s:21:"Clinical Psychologist";}s:38:"_add_a_new_staff_member_8_member_title";a:1:{i:0;s:19:"field_55acc8bcc8efb";}s:36:"add_a_new_staff_member_8_member_list";a:1:{i:0;s:1:"1";}s:37:"_add_a_new_staff_member_8_member_list";a:1:{i:0;s:19:"field_55acc906c8efc";}s:35:"add_a_new_staff_member_8_member_bio";a:1:{i:0;s:332:"Trevor is an exceptionally well trained, experienced, and effective clinical psychologist, who has worked over the last 25 years in both public hospital and private practice settings.

His current expertise is in cognitive behaviour therapy (including acceptance and commitment therapy) clinical hypnosis and mindfulness training.";}s:36:"_add_a_new_staff_member_8_member_bio";a:1:{i:0;s:19:"field_55acca62c8efe";}s:40:"add_a_new_staff_member_8_member_bio_more";a:1:{i:0;s:1778:"Trevor is highly skilled in the successful treatment of: generalised anxiety, panic attacks, social anxiety, post-traumatic stress disorder, health anxiety, obsessive compulsive disorder, low mood and depression (including bipolar disorder) anger difficulties, poor self-esteem, lack of confidence, addictions, stress-related illnesses, chronic pain, eating disorders, adjustment to injury and work related stress.</p>

<p>He graduated with an Honours degree in Psychology from the University of Hull in 1985 (receiving a prize for his final year studies) before being awarded a postgraduate scholarship to study at Edinburgh University. He graduated from Edinburgh University in 1990 with a Masters Degree in Clinical Psychology.</p>

<p>Further studies have included: (i) clinical hypnosis at Sheffield University (ii) cognitive therapy at the nationally renowned Newcastle Cognitive Therapy Centre, for which he was awarded their post graduate diploma and (iii) the receiving of a Doctorate in Clinical Psychology from Cardiff University in 2001, for his pioneering work in the field of mindfulness training.</p>

